result.execSummary:
The defendant Jacob J Rangel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manuf/Deliver Cocaine (>5-15g) [Modifiers: Second or Subsequent Offense, PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(cm)2.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Statutory costs assessed.  If supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.

Must not possess or consume any alcohol or controlled substances except by prescription. Random UA's are authorized. Any counseling and/or assessments deemed appropriate by agent. Must obtain and maintain full time verifiable employment. Must comply with all orders of family court; specifically pertaining to child support. No contact with any known drug dealers or users. Firearm warning given. Voting is prohibited until sentence is complete and civil rights are restored. Defendant must obey all rules and regulations while on supervision.

timeConds.notes: Must serve 15 days. Huber is granted for employment. Do not report late or under the influence of alcohol or controlled substances. Absolute sobriety is required. 45 days are stayed.
